On Tue, 4 Feb 2003, Robert S. Williams, MD wrote:

> Let me get this straight:
>
> The type 1 single port 1600cc engine yeilds 57 Horsepower

On a good day.

> The Type 1 dual port 1600cc engine yeilds 60 HP

On a good day.

> the Type 4 2000 cc engine yeilds 67 HP

Very reliably, and probably with more torque at a lower RPM.

> So, they all seem to offer very close HP ratings ..... Am I right? What is
> the big advantage of type 4 engines other than Fuel injection and hydraulic
> lifters? Especially when it seems the cost of parts is like double that of a
> type 1 engine.

Type IVs are a newer design with many refinements.  They will last much
longer in a bus application.  The bottom ends are very strong and don't
pound out like a type 1.

George
